==English==
===Pronunciation===

'''frac*tion'''
*[[IPA]]: /'frækʃən/
*[[SAMPA]]: /"fr{kS=n/
FRAAHK-shun
===Etymology===

French from Latin ''[[fractio]]'', '''breaking''', from ''[[frangere]]'', '''break'''


===Noun===
'''{{PAGENAME}}'''
# a part of a whole
# (''Mathematics'') a [[rational number]] written as two [[integer]]s, one over the other and separated by a horizontal bar called a [[solidus]], or side by side and separated by a [[slash]]; or in [[decimal notation]] using a [[decimal point]].
# a tiny part-"a fraction of the cost"
# part of a particular society or group.

